  "doc_id": "32545",
  "text": "The transport of the water molecules through the nanopores is also seen as intermittent, i.e., the pore mouth has to be filled with water, followed by entry into the channel and then chain transport. This process is sensitive to the pore radius, and as the pore wall radius fluctuates due to the fluctuations in the pore wall attraction distances, the liquid can either enter or be excluded dependent on the critical pore radius [CITATION_1] and the fluctuation in the filled and empty state of the nanochannel [CITATION_2] .",
